The maturity of any loan guaranteed or insured hereunder shall not exceed thirty years.
(Pub. L. 93–262, title II, § 210, Apr. 12, 1974, 88 Stat. 80.)</akn:p></akn:content></akn:section></akn:body></akn:act></akn:akomaNtoso>